resent a new gold standard and the best way forward, while others insist that these methods carry inherent inconsistencies, limitations, or ethical dilemmas that observational approaches do not. This unique collection of essays by the most influential figures on every side of this debate reveals its most important stakes and will provide useful guidance to students and scholars in many disciplines.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSocial sciencesxResearchxMethodology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Methodology.2bisacsh1 aBanerjee, Abhijit V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarrett, Christopher B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarter, Michael R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeaton, Angus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDuflo, Esther, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGelman, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerber, Alan S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreen, Donald P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aImai, Kosuke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaplan, Edward H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLangan Teele, Dawn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShapiro, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStokes, Susan C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStuart, Elizabeth A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTeele, Dawn Langan, eeditor.4edt4http://